1
00:00:12,417 --> 00:00:14,436
Expecting Mother

2
00:00:18,506 --> 00:00:19,732
Anno.

3
00:00:20,553 --> 00:00:21,700
What?

4
00:00:21,700 --> 00:00:23,820
Did you put away the tent on the roof?

5
00:00:24,873 --> 00:00:26,287
I'll do it tomorrow.

6
00:00:26,380 --> 00:00:29,600
You said that last time too.
Do it now!

7
00:00:29,600 --> 00:00:32,487
Yeah, yeah, yeah. Fine.

8
00:00:32,700 --> 00:00:33,900
Huh? What?

9
00:00:35,980 --> 00:00:38,016
Chief, get a wheelchair.

10
00:00:38,953 --> 00:00:40,163
Got it.

11
00:00:41,447 --> 00:00:42,647
What's wrong?

12
00:00:47,120 --> 00:00:49,425
Blood pressure is 129 over 62.

13
00:00:49,425 --> 00:00:53,320
Vitals are stable.
It was probably just a dizzy spell.

14
00:00:53,803 --> 00:00:56,600
I came for a checkup and got lightheaded.

15
00:00:56,600 --> 00:00:59,680
Blood pressure tends to fluctuate
during pregnancy.

16
00:01:02,310 --> 00:01:06,163
I'm sorry to cause trouble for the ER staff.

17
00:01:06,400 --> 00:01:08,816
No, we're glad you're all right.

18
00:01:09,380 --> 00:01:10,460
Dr. Daikoku.

19
00:01:10,460 --> 00:01:11,662
What?

20
00:01:11,870 --> 00:01:13,150
Nurse Sanpo.

21
00:01:13,150 --> 00:01:14,356
What?

22
00:01:14,500 --> 00:01:19,063
Dr. Anno, thank you so much as always.

23
00:01:19,150 --> 00:01:22,496
Huh? How do you know our names?

24
00:01:24,960 --> 00:01:29,187
Oh, I'm sorry.
I should have introduced myself sooner.

25
00:01:30,258 --> 00:01:33,343
My husband works with you.

26
00:01:33,538 --> 00:01:34,878
Your husband?

27
00:01:39,740 --> 00:01:41,943
I've finished my ICU rounds--

28
00:01:43,686 --> 00:01:44,886
Misuzu?

29
00:01:46,833 --> 00:01:50,899
Wait, your husband is Dr. Bonten?

30
00:01:52,740 --> 00:01:53,946
Yes.

31
00:01:54,860 --> 00:01:56,500
Which means...

32
00:01:57,860 --> 00:01:59,136
I'm his wife.

33
00:02:02,212 --> 00:02:06,116
Misuzu Bonten

34
00:02:06,830 --> 00:02:08,530
Dr. Daikoku.

35
00:02:08,530 --> 00:02:11,550
I had overlapping deliveries
and got held up.

36
00:02:11,550 --> 00:02:13,743
Thanks for coming.
She's right there.

37
00:02:14,196 --> 00:02:17,689
- Dr. Senju, sorry to trouble you.
- Not at all.

38
00:02:18,330 --> 00:02:19,843
How are you feeling?

39
00:02:19,909 --> 00:02:21,370
Much better now.

40
00:02:21,470 --> 00:02:22,930
Good.

41
00:02:22,930 --> 00:02:25,716
Dr. Senju, please take care of my wife.

42
00:02:25,716 --> 00:02:27,116
You can leave her to me.

43
00:02:27,770 --> 00:02:29,123
- Let's go.
- Okay.

44
00:02:47,643 --> 00:02:50,950
Dr. Bonten, I heard you're having a baby.

45
00:02:52,330 --> 00:02:53,670
Yes.

46
00:02:53,870 --> 00:02:56,630
Welcome to the Dad Club.

47
00:02:57,010 --> 00:02:58,219
Yes.

48
00:02:58,390 --> 00:03:00,246
When's the due date?

49
00:03:00,946 --> 00:03:05,030
She's 35 weeks now. Due next month.

50
00:03:05,110 --> 00:03:06,450
That's so soon.

51
00:03:06,450 --> 00:03:08,130
Is it a boy or a girl?

52
00:03:08,690 --> 00:03:09,830
A girl.

53
00:03:09,830 --> 00:03:12,256
A girl. How exciting!

54
00:03:12,493 --> 00:03:17,213
My wife and I are both getting up there
in age, so we have our worries.

55
00:03:18,305 --> 00:03:21,299
It's our first child
and everything is new to us.

56
00:03:22,476 --> 00:03:26,263
With geriatric pregnancy,
you do have to be more careful.

57
00:03:26,716 --> 00:03:27,950
Yes.

58
00:03:29,150 --> 00:03:32,556
Here's hoping for a healthy delivery.

59
00:03:34,483 --> 00:03:35,983
Thank you.

60
00:03:41,430 --> 00:03:45,030
Hey. Do you know how Dr. Bonten
and his wife met?

61
00:03:45,036 --> 00:03:46,670
No, I don't.

62
00:03:46,670 --> 00:03:51,910
His wife felt dizzy outdoors, and Dr. Bonten
happened to pass by and helped her.

63
00:03:51,910 --> 00:03:55,215
How lovely! What a fateful encounter.

64
00:03:55,215 --> 00:03:56,430
Right?

65
00:03:56,430 --> 00:03:57,890
So romantic!

66
00:03:59,370 --> 00:04:01,564
I'm jealous.

67
00:04:05,750 --> 00:04:08,190
I want to get married too.

68
00:04:09,603 --> 00:04:10,803
Tamotsu!

69
00:04:13,690 --> 00:04:16,670
If I did, I'd have tied the knot ages ago.

70
00:04:16,990 --> 00:04:19,190
Do you have a girlfriend, Dr. Yakushiji?

71
00:04:19,430 --> 00:04:22,290
No, I don't.

72
00:04:22,890 --> 00:04:27,410
I guess there's no time for romance
when you're in the ER.

73
00:04:27,450 --> 00:04:29,884
Sleep over dates, always.

74
00:04:29,884 --> 00:04:31,538
You've had one before, right?

75
00:04:31,723 --> 00:04:32,924
Huh?

76
00:04:34,690 --> 00:04:36,163
Well...

77
00:04:36,910 --> 00:04:39,776
Hey. What were you young folks
chatting about?

78
00:04:39,870 --> 00:04:41,316
Marriage.

79
00:04:41,830 --> 00:04:44,270
How I want to get married and be happy soon.

80
00:04:44,823 --> 00:04:46,029
How naive.

81
00:04:46,743 --> 00:04:50,099
Marriage doesn't automatically
make you happy.

82
00:04:50,286 --> 00:04:53,490
For men, marriage is a point system.

83
00:04:53,615 --> 00:04:56,350
Take out the trash? Plus one point.

84
00:04:56,437 --> 00:04:59,059
Drop off the kids? Plus two points.

85
00:04:59,213 --> 00:05:02,779
Forget your anniversary? Minus fifty points.

86
00:05:04,270 --> 00:05:11,450
Even if fate brought you together,
keeping it going takes effort--

87
00:05:15,576 --> 00:05:18,342
Yeah, I'm used to getting this reaction.

88
00:05:19,563 --> 00:05:20,763
So hot!

89
00:05:27,403 --> 00:05:29,696
Sorry to bother you during your meal.

90
00:05:31,106 --> 00:05:32,366
This is impressive.

91
00:05:35,019 --> 00:05:37,872
Thank you for earlier.

92
00:05:41,423 --> 00:05:42,683
Um...

93
00:05:44,930 --> 00:05:46,130
What?

94
00:05:47,850 --> 00:05:51,570
Is my husband being helpful
to everyone here?

95
00:05:52,956 --> 00:05:58,283
As you may know,
he's actually very timid and anxious.

96
00:05:58,588 --> 00:06:02,610
So, I'm always worried if
he isn't causing all of you any trouble.

97
00:06:04,410 --> 00:06:06,510
I don't think he's been any trouble.

98
00:06:06,710 --> 00:06:08,043
Oh, good.

99
00:06:09,023 --> 00:06:11,256
When he was in Cardiac Surgery,

100
00:06:11,596 --> 00:06:14,963
he always seemed cornered
and overwhelmed.

101
00:06:17,243 --> 00:06:20,723
But now he's full of life every day.

102
00:06:22,170 --> 00:06:25,240
I think it's thanks to all of you.

103
00:06:27,227 --> 00:06:28,653
Dr. Anno.

104
00:06:29,619 --> 00:06:32,916
Please continue to look after my husband.

105
00:07:31,260 --> 00:07:33,126
Oh, no!

106
00:07:58,756 --> 00:08:00,750
Hey! What are you doing?

107
00:08:02,010 --> 00:08:05,730
I told you to take this away.
Hey, stop that!

108
00:08:10,650 --> 00:08:11,856
Incoming.

109
00:08:14,887 --> 00:08:17,373
Dr. Ashura

110
00:08:19,833 --> 00:08:22,040
Call radiology.
I'm going to examine her.

111
00:08:22,273 --> 00:08:24,900
Struck by a car that jumped the sidewalk.

112
00:08:25,016 --> 00:08:28,200
She's conscious but barely
responding to our calls.

113
00:08:28,200 --> 00:08:29,520
What do you mean?

114
00:08:29,520 --> 00:08:32,376
She doesn't respond to any of our questions.

115
00:08:35,605 --> 00:08:39,272
Do you understand me?
Can you say your name?

116
00:08:41,500 --> 00:08:44,403
Could she be too shocked
and confused to speak?

117
00:08:44,496 --> 00:08:45,849
That's possible.

118
00:08:53,550 --> 00:08:55,103
She might not be hearing us.

119
00:08:55,103 --> 00:08:56,303
What?

120
00:08:57,429 --> 00:08:59,342
- Get a writing pad.
- Yes, Doctor.

121
00:09:01,469 --> 00:09:03,510
Fluid accumulation in the chest.

122
00:09:16,340 --> 00:09:18,230
I'm Dr. Bonten.

123
00:09:19,932 --> 00:09:24,576
This is Dr. Anno,
who'll also be treating you.

124
00:09:29,856 --> 00:09:31,082
Asuka.

125
00:09:32,520 --> 00:09:35,302
Doctor, is my daughter going to be all right?

126
00:09:35,440 --> 00:09:39,500
She'll need to stay hospitalized for a while,
but her life isn't in danger.

127
00:09:40,540 --> 00:09:41,788
Thank goodness.

128
00:09:42,680 --> 00:09:44,366
Thank you so much.

129
00:09:46,330 --> 00:09:48,250
I'm glad you're safe.

130
00:09:50,802 --> 00:09:53,322
Are you okay?
Does it hurt anywhere?

131
00:09:53,562 --> 00:09:54,829
I'm fine.

132
00:09:56,023 --> 00:09:58,070
I'm fine. Go home.

133
00:10:01,276 --> 00:10:02,476
Now!

134
00:10:03,753 --> 00:10:04,986
All right.

135
00:10:06,020 --> 00:10:08,736
I'm sorry,
I'll head home for today.

136
00:10:09,883 --> 00:10:12,410
Please take care of my daughter.

137
00:10:14,063 --> 00:10:17,543
See you. Happy birthday.

138
00:10:46,890 --> 00:10:48,350
Thanks for the dishes.

139
00:10:48,750 --> 00:10:50,363
You're welcome.

140
00:10:50,890 --> 00:10:52,098
Oh, yeah.

141
00:10:53,131 --> 00:10:57,610
They took this picture
at my checkup today.

142
00:10:59,170 --> 00:11:00,443
Thanks.

143
00:11:03,775 --> 00:11:06,493
I can see the face much better
than last time.

144
00:11:06,493 --> 00:11:08,950
Yeah. They said everything's
progressing well.

145
00:11:09,567 --> 00:11:12,707
We'll get to meet this little one soon.

146
00:11:12,707 --> 00:11:13,907
Yeah.

147
00:11:16,610 --> 00:11:17,821
Taro.

148
00:11:19,450 --> 00:11:22,574
Because I couldn't get pregnant for so long,

149
00:11:23,291 --> 00:11:26,477
I thought maybe I wasn't
meant to be a mother.

150
00:11:28,750 --> 00:11:33,389
But this child chose to come to us.

151
00:11:36,123 --> 00:11:38,376
I'm so glad we never gave up.

152
00:11:38,840 --> 00:11:40,830
Yeah. Me too.

153
00:11:42,120 --> 00:11:44,377
But now I can't help feeling anxious.

154
00:11:46,520 --> 00:11:50,140
Will this baby will be born safely?

155
00:11:52,960 --> 00:11:56,784
What happened today,
and the risks of geriatric pregnancy.

156
00:11:57,578 --> 00:11:59,758
All I can think about are the risks.

157
00:12:03,510 --> 00:12:05,750
Sorry. I shouldn't have brought that up.

158
00:12:06,010 --> 00:12:07,283
No.

159
00:12:07,654 --> 00:12:09,990
I hope the baby's born healthy and strong.

160
00:12:10,756 --> 00:12:11,962
Yeah.

161
00:12:13,036 --> 00:12:17,010
Oh, hold on. Let me take a picture of this.

162
00:12:17,156 --> 00:12:18,756
A photo?

163
00:12:19,406 --> 00:12:21,759
Taishaku General Hospital

164
00:12:22,352 --> 00:12:23,772
Are you in any pain?

165
00:12:29,070 --> 00:12:31,596
Is anything troubling you?

166
00:12:38,430 --> 00:12:40,763
Let me know if you need anything!

167
00:12:40,946 --> 00:12:42,966
Right. Okay then.

168
00:12:46,048 --> 00:12:49,440
Thank you for your help.
How is my daughter doing?

169
00:12:50,020 --> 00:12:52,397
She's fine. Recovering well.

170
00:12:52,740 --> 00:12:54,180
Thank you.

171
00:12:57,394 --> 00:12:59,461
Did you sleep okay last night?

172
00:13:00,674 --> 00:13:02,593
Did you eat? Take your medicine?

173
00:13:02,593 --> 00:13:03,793
I'm fine.

174
00:13:04,882 --> 00:13:06,703
You don't have to come.

175
00:13:17,090 --> 00:13:18,389
Don't say that!

176
00:13:41,824 --> 00:13:43,029
Excuse me.

177
00:13:45,151 --> 00:13:47,977
Things seem pretty serious
with the Doi family.

178
00:13:48,411 --> 00:13:50,924
Asuka's been really withdrawn.

179
00:13:51,520 --> 00:13:54,120
His wife passed away, right?

180
00:13:54,300 --> 00:13:55,659
That's what I heard.

181
00:13:55,706 --> 00:13:57,053
She's at that age.

182
00:13:57,152 --> 00:14:00,679
Even without her hearing issue,
it would be tough.

183
00:14:01,040 --> 00:14:02,246
Yes.

184
00:14:50,976 --> 00:14:52,800
List of kanji and names

185
00:15:00,650 --> 00:15:02,980
Hey, how about Yui?

186
00:15:03,147 --> 00:15:06,211
It means "cherishing the bonds
between people."

187
00:15:09,170 --> 00:15:11,325
Are you okay? Is something wrong?

188
00:15:12,598 --> 00:15:14,265
No, it's nothing.

189
00:15:17,665 --> 00:15:21,219
Yui, huh? That's a lovely name.

190
00:15:21,219 --> 00:15:22,426
Right?

191
00:15:22,811 --> 00:15:26,750
A name is something
this child carries for life.

192
00:15:26,750 --> 00:15:27,775
Yeah.

193
00:15:27,775 --> 00:15:31,850
I keep filling it with hopes
for the kind of life I want for her.

194
00:15:32,163 --> 00:15:35,430
When you put it that way,
it's even harder to narrow down.

195
00:15:35,490 --> 00:15:37,883
Oh, she kicked.

196
00:15:37,883 --> 00:15:39,083
Really?

197
00:15:40,156 --> 00:15:41,902
See? She's full of energy.

198
00:15:41,902 --> 00:15:43,222
Yeah, she is.

199
00:15:44,122 --> 00:15:48,930
Mommy will protect you no matter what, okay?

200
00:15:53,566 --> 00:15:56,725
Birthday

201
00:16:01,368 --> 00:16:02,568
Birthday

202
00:16:17,377 --> 00:16:19,346
Mother and Child Health Handbook

203
00:16:31,888 --> 00:16:34,421
It's a girl!

204
00:16:38,011 --> 00:16:39,853
Records of Pregnancy

205
00:16:39,853 --> 00:16:43,881
I'm the happiest in my life right now.

206
00:17:05,613 --> 00:17:06,993
Hello.

207
00:17:18,690 --> 00:17:22,110
You caught me at an embarrassing moment.

208
00:17:22,723 --> 00:17:23,929
Not at all.

209
00:17:26,198 --> 00:17:31,283
I'm her father,
yet I hesitate to even go see her.

210
00:17:33,221 --> 00:17:34,809
How embarrassing.

211
00:17:40,996 --> 00:17:42,963
Is Asuka all right?

212
00:17:43,983 --> 00:17:46,416
She's fine. Please don't worry.

213
00:17:49,173 --> 00:17:50,676
I'm relieved.

214
00:17:52,815 --> 00:17:57,500
This may not be my place to ask,

215
00:17:58,460 --> 00:18:02,230
but what were you talking about
with your daughter yesterday?

216
00:18:10,257 --> 00:18:12,221
Did you sleep okay last night?

217
00:18:13,250 --> 00:18:15,330
Did you eat? Take your medicine?

218
00:18:15,330 --> 00:18:16,530
I'm fine.

219
00:18:17,063 --> 00:18:18,886
You don't have to come.

220
00:18:19,036 --> 00:18:21,156
You must be busy.

221
00:18:21,511 --> 00:18:22,971
Don't worry about me.

222
00:18:22,971 --> 00:18:27,014
Don't put yourself off like that.

223
00:18:32,957 --> 00:18:35,256
It's all my fault.

224
00:18:39,390 --> 00:18:41,710
Don't overthink like that.

225
00:18:41,897 --> 00:18:45,836
The accident was because of
the driver's carelessness.

226
00:18:46,348 --> 00:18:47,855
You didn't do anything wrong.

227
00:18:47,855 --> 00:18:49,394
No. It was my fault.

228
00:18:49,497 --> 00:18:53,883
Why else would something like this happen
on Mom's death anniversary?

229
00:18:53,883 --> 00:18:55,942
It's because everything's my fault.

230
00:18:58,563 --> 00:19:02,223
I'm always causing you trouble.

231
00:19:02,537 --> 00:19:06,152
Mom died because she gave birth to me.

232
00:19:06,672 --> 00:19:08,312
That wasn't your fault.

233
00:19:08,312 --> 00:19:10,198
I've told you countless times.

234
00:19:14,690 --> 00:19:17,313
I should never have been born.

235
00:19:17,313 --> 00:19:18,670
Don't say that!

236
00:19:22,620 --> 00:19:26,040
Your wife passed away during childbirth.

237
00:19:29,560 --> 00:19:34,020
I've told Asuka countless times
it wasn't her fault.

238
00:19:35,623 --> 00:19:36,881
But...

239
00:19:39,250 --> 00:19:45,003
Deep down, she may have sensed
that I was still grieving my wife.

240
00:19:46,150 --> 00:19:49,710
She must have felt it all along.

241
00:19:51,890 --> 00:19:56,010
Even without her hearing,
even without a mother,

242
00:19:56,743 --> 00:19:59,830
I wanted her to live her life
looking forward.

243
00:20:01,090 --> 00:20:04,423
I tried my best in my own way.

244
00:20:07,206 --> 00:20:09,879
To think I made her feel that way...

245
00:20:11,603 --> 00:20:14,330
I can't face my wife in the afterlife.

246
00:20:49,030 --> 00:20:51,609
I have no parents.

247
00:21:00,143 --> 00:21:03,950
Someone precious can vanish without warning.

248
00:21:27,750 --> 00:21:30,270
Modern Obstetrics

249
00:21:34,574 --> 00:21:36,240
- Good work today.
- Good work.

250
00:21:36,240 --> 00:21:38,500
Oh, studying obstetrics?
Good for you.

251
00:21:39,040 --> 00:21:41,282
Figured I should brush up on it.

252
00:21:41,482 --> 00:21:44,760
But honestly, I don't understand
pregnant patients at all.

253
00:21:44,980 --> 00:21:49,430
Childbirth's outside our specialty too.
I'm clueless myself.

254
00:21:49,550 --> 00:21:52,480
You have a midwife license, right?

255
00:21:52,480 --> 00:21:53,953
Technically, yes.

256
00:21:54,132 --> 00:21:57,240
But I've been in emergency medicine
so long, I'm rusty too.

257
00:21:57,540 --> 00:22:01,145
Midwives also deliver babies, right?

258
00:22:01,800 --> 00:22:03,380
For normal deliveries, yes.

259
00:22:03,843 --> 00:22:07,510
But if the mother or baby
needs medical intervention,

260
00:22:07,510 --> 00:22:09,627
OB or pediatric doctors step in.

261
00:22:09,780 --> 00:22:14,240
Man, it's a whole other world to me.

262
00:22:14,420 --> 00:22:18,030
Bringing new life into the world
is no easy feat.

263
00:22:39,210 --> 00:22:42,996
Your daughter is waiting.

264
00:22:57,723 --> 00:23:00,631
I have no parents.
Someone precious can vanish without warning.

265
00:23:00,631 --> 00:23:04,506
If you have something to say,
you should tell them.

266
00:23:32,697 --> 00:23:34,594
I'm sorry.

267
00:23:39,070 --> 00:23:40,750
You don't need to apologize.

268
00:23:41,510 --> 00:23:45,423
I should be the one to apologize.

269
00:23:57,670 --> 00:23:59,850
Mother and Child Health Handbook

270
00:24:12,069 --> 00:24:15,321
Mother and Child Health Handbook

271
00:24:28,583 --> 00:24:30,317
Today, we chose your name: Asuka.

272
00:24:30,317 --> 00:24:33,363
No matter how hard today is,
may flowers bloom tomorrow.

273
00:24:33,363 --> 00:24:35,408
May your life always hold such hope.

274
00:24:35,408 --> 00:24:39,087
With that wish, this name is
a gift from your father and mother.

275
00:25:02,714 --> 00:25:05,563
From now on, I will protect you
for your mother too.

276
00:25:05,563 --> 00:25:08,563
I will protect you.

277
00:25:22,597 --> 00:25:27,765
From now on, I will protect you
for your mother too.

278
00:25:55,163 --> 00:25:57,850
I'm...

279
00:26:01,688 --> 00:26:05,101
happy to be born

280
00:26:07,790 --> 00:26:10,356
as your and Mom's

281
00:26:17,640 --> 00:26:20,243
child.

282
00:26:27,176 --> 00:26:29,730
I'm glad

283
00:26:29,877 --> 00:26:32,103
I was born to you.

284
00:26:37,510 --> 00:26:41,550
Thank you for being born

285
00:26:44,783 --> 00:26:47,430
as our child.

286
00:26:48,683 --> 00:26:51,183
Thank you for coming

287
00:26:52,010 --> 00:26:54,168
into our lives.

288
00:27:18,353 --> 00:27:19,914
- Good work today.
- You too.

289
00:27:19,914 --> 00:27:21,528
See you.

290
00:27:23,800 --> 00:27:25,683
- Good work, Doctor.
- Good work.

291
00:27:38,480 --> 00:27:41,358
Dr. Anno, thank you.

292
00:27:43,750 --> 00:27:48,956
I couldn't understand what
those two were saying,

293
00:27:50,530 --> 00:27:52,996
but I think they'll be just fine now.

294
00:27:55,480 --> 00:27:56,710
Good.

295
00:27:57,753 --> 00:27:59,080
Good work today.

296
00:28:01,590 --> 00:28:04,637
Got it. Be careful.
Okay, see you.

297
00:28:21,719 --> 00:28:23,079
I'm home.

298
00:28:27,526 --> 00:28:28,827
Misuzu?

299
00:28:35,816 --> 00:28:37,103
Misuzu?

300
00:28:40,520 --> 00:28:41,743
Misuzu.

301
00:28:45,456 --> 00:28:46,680
Misuzu.

302
00:28:46,898 --> 00:28:50,116
I think I'm bleeding internally.

303
00:28:51,860 --> 00:28:54,826
It's okay.
Let's get to the hospital now.

304
00:28:58,092 --> 00:28:59,120
Yes.

305
00:28:59,120 --> 00:29:00,233
Dr. Anno.

306
00:29:00,233 --> 00:29:01,720
Dr. Bonten? What's wrong?

307
00:29:01,860 --> 00:29:04,246
My wife collapsed at home.

308
00:29:04,323 --> 00:29:05,526
What?

309
00:29:05,809 --> 00:29:08,003
She has bleeding and abdominal pain.

310
00:29:08,946 --> 00:29:10,196
Bring her in now.

311
00:29:11,315 --> 00:29:14,520
We may need emergency surgery.
Contact OB, pediatrics, and the OR.

312
00:29:14,520 --> 00:29:15,726
Understood.

313
00:29:20,730 --> 00:29:21,943
Misuzu.

314
00:29:24,680 --> 00:29:26,033
Turning around.

315
00:29:28,400 --> 00:29:29,683
Stepping back.

316
00:29:30,060 --> 00:29:31,880
On three. One, two, three.

317
00:29:33,230 --> 00:29:34,550
Palpating the abdomen.

318
00:29:38,750 --> 00:29:41,443
It's hard. Board-like rigidity.

319
00:29:48,063 --> 00:29:49,882
Fetal heart rate is dropping.

320
00:29:49,882 --> 00:29:52,830
The baby's not getting oxygen.
Maternal vitals?

321
00:29:52,830 --> 00:29:56,710
BP 80 over 52. Pulse in the 120s.
She's in shock.

322
00:29:57,316 --> 00:30:01,009
Bleeding, fetal heart rate abnormality,
and sudden abdominal pain.

323
00:30:02,644 --> 00:30:04,437
Placental abruption.

324
00:30:05,984 --> 00:30:07,269
Where's OB?

325
00:30:07,269 --> 00:30:08,497
I'll go check.

326
00:30:16,610 --> 00:30:17,910
Misuzu.

327
00:30:17,935 --> 00:30:20,608
Please. Save us.

328
00:30:22,390 --> 00:30:26,376
You'll be fine. I promise.

329
00:30:27,016 --> 00:30:30,110
Our baby.

330
00:30:33,710 --> 00:30:35,039
Please save her.

331
00:30:44,395 --> 00:30:45,660
Misuzu.

332
00:30:45,660 --> 00:30:47,690
A detached placenta can't reattach.

333
00:30:47,813 --> 00:30:53,276
The baby is already oxygen-deprived
and in critical danger. We might lose it.

334
00:30:54,746 --> 00:30:55,920
No.

335
00:30:55,920 --> 00:30:59,240
An emergency C-section
is the only way to save them.

336
00:31:02,740 --> 00:31:04,056
Doctor Anno.

337
00:31:04,199 --> 00:31:08,126
Dr. Senju is handling another emergency
and can't come.

338
00:31:09,740 --> 00:31:12,980
Her vitals could flatline at any moment.

339
00:31:13,814 --> 00:31:16,418
We should transfer her to a hospital
that can help.

340
00:31:16,418 --> 00:31:18,748
- There's no time for that.
- Then what?

341
00:31:18,961 --> 00:31:21,340
This isn't a routine C-section.

342
00:31:22,364 --> 00:31:24,690
She could hemorrhage the moment we open.

343
00:31:26,660 --> 00:31:29,280
This is beyond us.

344
00:31:34,516 --> 00:31:35,716
Misuzu.

345
00:31:38,919 --> 00:31:43,830
Mommy will protect you no matter what.

346
00:31:48,823 --> 00:31:50,063
Please.

347
00:31:53,940 --> 00:31:55,470
Please save my wife

348
00:31:57,540 --> 00:31:59,807
and my daughter.

349
00:32:08,510 --> 00:32:10,083
We're not transferring her.

350
00:32:13,413 --> 00:32:15,216
I'm doing the C-section now.

351
00:32:19,607 --> 00:32:20,807
Okay.

352
00:32:21,076 --> 00:32:22,893
- Bring her to the OR.
- Okay.

353
00:32:27,624 --> 00:32:29,044
Operation in Progress

354
00:32:32,500 --> 00:32:33,813
Here.

355
00:32:42,530 --> 00:32:43,903
Let's begin.

356
00:32:43,930 --> 00:32:45,196
Ready.

357
00:32:45,270 --> 00:32:46,836
- Scalpel.
- Yes.

358
00:32:56,574 --> 00:32:57,794
Uterine incision.

359
00:33:04,250 --> 00:33:05,730
More bleeding than expected.

360
00:33:05,730 --> 00:33:06,962
- Suction.
- Yes.

361
00:33:13,236 --> 00:33:14,743
- Delivering now.
- Yes.

362
00:33:30,563 --> 00:33:31,850
Clamps.

363
00:33:37,830 --> 00:33:39,030
Here.

364
00:33:43,093 --> 00:33:44,559
- Take over.
- Okay.

365
00:33:46,100 --> 00:33:47,513
Forceps.

366
00:33:55,128 --> 00:33:56,328
She's not crying.

367
00:33:58,015 --> 00:33:59,080
Cry.

368
00:33:59,080 --> 00:34:00,186
Please.

369
00:34:00,186 --> 00:34:01,391
Cry.

370
00:34:02,600 --> 00:34:04,090
Cry, please.

371
00:34:04,090 --> 00:34:05,290
Cry.

372
00:34:13,357 --> 00:34:14,557
Cry.

373
00:34:27,360 --> 00:34:28,793
Thank you.

374
00:34:33,000 --> 00:34:34,720
Congratulations.

375
00:34:43,723 --> 00:34:44,856
Atonic hemorrhage.

376
00:34:44,856 --> 00:34:47,763
- We must stop the bleeding now.
- Compression hemostasis.

377
00:34:47,763 --> 00:34:50,803
- More transfusions. Administer oxytocin.
- Yes.

378
00:34:51,057 --> 00:34:52,257
Misuzu.

379
00:34:53,296 --> 00:34:54,656
- Suction.
- Yes.

380
00:35:00,286 --> 00:35:02,480
Heart rate is dropping.
It's in the 50s.

381
00:35:02,480 --> 00:35:03,966
The bleeding won't stop.

382
00:35:03,966 --> 00:35:05,720
She'll go into cardiac arrest.

383
00:35:07,460 --> 00:35:08,643
Keep suctioning.

384
00:35:08,643 --> 00:35:09,843
Yes.

385
00:35:10,699 --> 00:35:12,340
Mommy's fighting hard.

386
00:35:12,700 --> 00:35:14,020
Root for her.

387
00:35:20,570 --> 00:35:22,570
Doctor, heart rate's in the 30s.

388
00:35:23,703 --> 00:35:25,343
Compression won't stop it.

389
00:35:25,490 --> 00:35:27,263
- I'm suturing.
- Okay.

390
00:35:38,669 --> 00:35:39,853
Cardiac arrest.

391
00:35:39,853 --> 00:35:40,920
Misuzu.

392
00:35:40,920 --> 00:35:41,960
Starting CPR.

393
00:35:41,960 --> 00:35:43,100
Administer adrenaline.

394
00:35:43,100 --> 00:35:45,543
- Take over the suturing.
- Got it. 0-Vicryl.

395
00:35:45,714 --> 00:35:47,153
- Please suction.
- Yes.

396
00:35:57,590 --> 00:35:59,110
Blood loss exceeded 5,000.

397
00:35:59,388 --> 00:36:00,950
Transfusions can't keep up.

398
00:36:06,100 --> 00:36:07,503
She's not coming back.

399
00:36:08,639 --> 00:36:09,876
Misuzu.

400
00:36:38,583 --> 00:36:39,944
Dr. Bonten.

401
00:36:42,080 --> 00:36:44,293
Your baby is screaming, "Don't give up!"

402
00:36:51,750 --> 00:36:56,370
She needs your voice too
to come back from the brink.

403
00:37:07,963 --> 00:37:09,310
Misuzu.

404
00:37:11,303 --> 00:37:13,863
Come on. Come back to me.

405
00:37:17,020 --> 00:37:19,483
Don't die on me, Misuzu.

406
00:37:23,180 --> 00:37:26,903
Please. Come back to me.

407
00:37:30,820 --> 00:37:32,238
Stay with me.

408
00:37:33,700 --> 00:37:36,976
You're going to be a mother.

409
00:37:37,023 --> 00:37:38,683
It's a girl!

410
00:37:41,745 --> 00:37:45,718
We're going to be a family.

411
00:37:48,736 --> 00:37:50,069
Misuzu.

412
00:37:52,063 --> 00:37:53,336
Misuzu.

413
00:37:55,131 --> 00:37:56,593
Misuzu!

414
00:38:29,256 --> 00:38:30,483
Heartbeat restored.

415
00:38:32,796 --> 00:38:34,470
- Continue hemostasis.
- Yes.

416
00:39:15,446 --> 00:39:16,723
Good morning.

417
00:39:17,145 --> 00:39:19,499
Good morning.

418
00:39:25,009 --> 00:39:28,856
Congratulations on the birth of your child!

419
00:39:33,770 --> 00:39:36,690
Your wife and baby both fought so hard.

420
00:39:37,289 --> 00:39:39,330
You went through a lot too.

421
00:39:41,530 --> 00:39:44,050
I look forward to being fellow dads together.

422
00:39:46,656 --> 00:39:48,088
Thank you, everyone.

423
00:39:49,024 --> 00:39:51,617
All right, let's have another great day!

424
00:39:51,617 --> 00:39:52,831
Yes, sir!

425
00:39:53,750 --> 00:39:55,310
What should the name be?

426
00:39:55,656 --> 00:39:57,696
Why are you the one to decide?

427
00:40:04,136 --> 00:40:05,416
Dr. Anno.

428
00:40:07,569 --> 00:40:11,135
You saved the lives of my wife and daughter.

429
00:40:13,274 --> 00:40:15,936
Thank you so much.

430
00:40:24,830 --> 00:40:26,110
Congratulations.

431
00:40:28,170 --> 00:40:29,370
I'm off on rounds.

432
00:40:29,370 --> 00:40:30,579
Okay.

433
00:40:34,850 --> 00:40:39,283
Thanks to all of you,
I was able to reconnect with my daughter.

434
00:40:41,754 --> 00:40:46,350
Just having Asuka makes
everything in my life brighter.

435
00:40:47,350 --> 00:40:49,976
Thank you so much.

436
00:41:04,696 --> 00:41:06,556
Thank you.

437
00:41:18,310 --> 00:41:19,510
Stay well.

438
00:41:22,377 --> 00:41:23,577
Dad.

439
00:41:24,763 --> 00:41:25,963
Get along.

440
00:41:27,137 --> 00:41:28,337
Mom.

441
00:41:29,110 --> 00:41:30,310
Watching.

442
00:41:37,897 --> 00:41:39,097
Thank you.

443
00:41:44,680 --> 00:41:46,756
We'll be going now.

444
00:41:57,070 --> 00:42:00,059
Dr. Anno, you know sign language?

445
00:42:00,059 --> 00:42:01,890
What did you say just now?

446
00:42:01,890 --> 00:42:03,236
Who knows?

447
00:42:13,930 --> 00:42:15,330
So cute.

448
00:42:16,130 --> 00:42:17,330
Yeah.

449
00:42:19,330 --> 00:42:22,870
She was born before
we could decide on a name.

450
00:42:26,930 --> 00:42:28,350
How about Hikari?

451
00:42:29,750 --> 00:42:30,983
Hikari?

452
00:42:32,210 --> 00:42:36,717
Just by being here,
she brightens our whole world.

453
00:42:38,165 --> 00:42:40,858
So tiny, yet she shines
so brightly for us.

454
00:42:43,286 --> 00:42:44,790
And not just for us.

455
00:42:45,750 --> 00:42:52,510
I hope she'll be a light for everyone
she meets along the way.

456
00:42:58,480 --> 00:42:59,920
Hikari.

457
00:43:03,913 --> 00:43:05,433
Hikari.

458
00:43:08,160 --> 00:43:10,716
Thank you for coming into our lives.

459
00:43:55,670 --> 00:43:57,126
Freedom's all you need.

460
00:43:57,126 --> 00:43:58,450
Tatsu.

461
00:43:58,500 --> 00:44:00,152
He lost consciousness.

462
00:44:00,152 --> 00:44:02,098
We're neighbors. Must be fate.

463
00:44:02,098 --> 00:44:04,044
May I have a word?

464
00:44:04,044 --> 00:44:05,905
Can you explain what's going on?

465
00:44:05,905 --> 00:44:06,980
Are you okay?

466
00:44:06,980 --> 00:44:08,360
Is it really that bad?

467
00:44:08,473 --> 00:44:09,779
Incoming.
